des:
If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us with email : support@yg-ai.com

The main function of the Light Strip Agent is to unleash the user's imagination. The user describes a scene, and the Agent, based on a large language model, completes the lighting expression of the user's scene. The Agent will simulate the user's expected scene through dynamic effects and colors and describe the effect in natural language.

If you have multiple LED strips, the Agent can better showcase its effects. You can define the installation position of each LED strip in the app, which can effectively enhance the Agent's expression capability.

No need to manually control your device - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 
The answer to the Light Strip Agent skill reply comes from whether the user controls the device successfully or unresponsively.
Connect Alexa and your Zigma smart devices by following steps:
(1). Download "Zigma" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Registered and login Zigma account in "Zigma" app;
(3). You need to have some Zigma smart devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in "Zigma" app and set the nickname of your devices(Easy to identify. The default is: robot, light, socket, etc.);
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Light Strip Agent" skill from the "Alexa" app skills categories;
(8). Click "Enable" button of "Light Strip Agent" skill, and you'll be navigated to Zigma login page;
(9). Input your Zigma account and password, "log in",you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
"Alexa, open light strip agent"
"Alexa, ask light strip agent to give me a blue color"
"Alexa, tell light strip agent I want a blue sky, white clouds, and green grass"
"Alexa, tell light strip agent I'm sitting by the sea, watching the sunset"
